acker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102865\nname: delta6-acyl-lipid desaturase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a gamma-linolenoyl-[glycerolipid] + 2 ferrocytochrome b5 + O2 + 2 H+ = a (9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dien-6-ynoyl-[glycerolipid] + 2 ferricytochrome b5 + 2 H2O.\" [GOC:pz, PMID:10848999, RHEA:46536]\nxref: EC:1.14.19.38 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8343\nxref: RHEA:46536 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016717 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102866\nname: acyl-lipid (8-3)-desaturase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: an (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-containing glycerolipid + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H+ + O2 = (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl-containing glycerolipid + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H2O. Also converts an (8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosatetraenoyl-containing glycerolipid into a (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z)-eicosapentaenoyl-containing glycerolipid.\" [EC:1.14.19.30]\nsynonym: \"acyl-lipid 5-desaturase activity\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"Delta(5)-fatty-acid desaturase activity\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"di-homo-gamma-linolenate delta5 desaturase activity\" RELATED []\nxref: EC:1.14.19.30 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8346 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8350 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:46260 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:46264 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016717 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102915\nname: piperitol synthase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + (+)-pinoresinol + NADPH + O2 = (+)-piperitol + NADP + 2 H2O.\" [EC:1.14.19.74, PMID:16785429]\nxref: EC:1.14.19.74 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8695 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8696 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:56776 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:56780 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016709 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen, NAD(P)H as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102963\nname: (S)-corytuberine synthase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + (S)-reticulinium(1+) + NADPH + O2 = (S)-corytuberine + NADP + 2 H2O.\" [PMID:18230623, RHEA:51540]\nxref: EC:1.14.19.51 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-9314\nxref: RHEA:51540 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016717 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/21133\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102985\nname: acyl-CoA (9+3)-desaturase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the introduction of a cis double bond at position 12 of fatty-acyl-CoAs that contain a cis double bond at position 9. Specific reactions include: (9Z)-hexadecenoyl-CoA + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H+ + O2 = (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl-CoA + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H2O; and (9Z)-hexadecenoyl-CoA + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome b5] + O2 + 2 H(+) = (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl-CoA + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome b5] + 2 H2O.\" [EC:1.14.19.6]\nsynonym: \"delta12-fatty-acid desaturase activity\" EXACT []\nxref: EC:1.14.19.6 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-9601 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-9616 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:25856 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:45096 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016215 ! acyl-CoA desaturase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28526\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29820\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102988\nname: acyl-CoA 15-desaturase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: (9Z,12Z)-hexadecadienoyl-CoA + O2 + a reduced electron acceptor = 9,12,15-cis-hexadecatrienoyl-CoA + 2 H2O + an oxidized electron acceptor.\" [EC:1.14.19.13]\nsynonym: \"9,12-cis-hexadecadienoic acid delta 15 desaturase activity\" EXACT []\nxref: EC:1.14.19.13 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-9617\nxref: RHEA:46232 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016215 ! acyl-CoA desaturase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29820\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30193\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0102993\nname: sn-2 acyl-lipid omega-3 desaturase (ferredoxin) activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalysis of the reaction: a (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl-containing glycerolipid + 2 H+ + O2 + 2 reduced [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin] = (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatrienoyl-containing glycerolipid + 2 H2O + 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S]-[ferredoxin]. Also converts a (7Z,10Z)-hexadecadienoyl-containing glycerolipid into a (7Z,10Z,13Z)-hexadecatrienoyl-containing glycerolipid.\" [EC:1.14.19.35]\ncomment: Introduces a cis double bond at a location 3 carbons away from the methyl end of the fatty acid. Acts on all 16:2- or 18:2-containing chloroplast membrane lipids, including phosphatidylglycerol, monogalactosyldiacylglycerol, digalactosyldiaclyglycerol, and sulfoquinovosyldiacylglycerol.\nsynonym: \"linolenate delta15 desaturase activity\" EXACT []\nxref: EC:1.14.19.35 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-1727 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8295 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8297 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8299 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8301 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8303 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8309 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8310 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8314 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8365 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-8366 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: MetaCyc:RXN-9667 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:46408 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:46412 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:66512 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:66516 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:66520 {source=\"skos:narrowMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016717 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on paired donors, with oxidation of a pair of donors resulting in the reduction of molecular oxygen to two molecules of water\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28070\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0106145\nname: scopoletin 8-hydroxylase activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Catalyzes of the reaction: scopoletin + 2-oxoglutarate+O2=fraxetin +succinate+ CO2).\" [GOC:lr, PMID:29361149, PMID:29581584, RHEA:57848]\nxref: EC:1.14.11.60 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nxref: RHEA:57848 {source=\"skos:exactMatch\"}\nis_a: GO:0016709 ! oxido